reviewText: The video showed most of the nudity expressed by the subject but there were no views of her delicate flower between her fine legs.  This compared poorly with the excellent coverage in Ocean Goddess and Zen Goddess.
Title: Pure Nude Yoga - Worship the Sun

reviewText: watching this was relaxing and enjoyable. a way to practice and learn to bend the body. they actually knew yoga.
Title: Pure Nude Yoga - Worship the Sun

reviewText: I saw the five star rating but was dissapointed, blaa blaa blaa boring. If you listen to the sounds of the ocean in alternative audio mode with your eyes closed this dvd is for you.
Title: Pure Nude Yoga - Worship the Sun

reviewText: The girl is young. She is cute. She is nude.  She does yoga in a rocky area next to what appears to be the ocean or a large lake. The camera work is pretty good. For some reason the camera on these two videos likes to shoot facing the sun so the model is often in her own shade. This video is better than the zen garden one by a long shot if you just want to watch, (and see what you are looking at). Even so, there are still a lot of silhouette shots because of the camera angle.There is no verbal cuing, but the name of the asana is flashed on the screen as the model goes into the pose.
Title: Pure Nude Yoga - Worship the Sun

reviewText: The first in a series of three (so far).  Performed by a twenty year old female model called Channel.  This model's practice/performance is ideal for the beginning student yogi.  Practice of these asanas with focus, effort and with awareness help one to find balance in mind body and spirit.  It's good.
Title: Pure Nude Yoga - Worship the Sun

reviewText: I love yoga now that I am getting older and find it better for my body than hard workouts. Seeing it done in the nude brings a different dimension to it. My own yoga personal trainer wears almost nothing (usually jog-bra and bikini bottom) so this is closer to my real life.
Title: Pure Nude Yoga - Worship the Sun
